subject: Sailboats and Sailing
Nineteen Hundred Thirties
America's Cup
lead_paragraph: Dorade, a 52-foot wooden sailboat considered the forebear of modern racing yachts, captured the Los Angeles-to-Honolulu race this week, echoing its 1936 victory.
